THIRD-PARTY COMPONENTS
======================

rustyweb bundles and serves software from the Webrecorder project. Webrecorder
did the hard part — the actual web archive replay — and rustyweb would not exist
without it. These components are included unmodified and remain under their own
license:

  ReplayWeb.page  (crates/rustyweb-lib/static/replay/ui.js)
  wabac.js + wombat (crates/rustyweb-lib/static/replay/sw.js)

    Copyright (C) 2020-2026, Webrecorder Software
    Licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 or later
    Source: https://github.com/webrecorder/replayweb.page
            https://github.com/webrecorder/wabac.js
    Bundled version: ReplayWeb.page 2.4.6 (wabac.js 2.26.4)

These files are fetched from the pinned upstream release by
scripts/fetch-replay.sh and are not modified by rustyweb. Their corresponding
source is available at the URLs above.

The ReplayWeb.page/wabac.js bundles themselves incorporate additional
third-party libraries under permissive licenses (MIT, BSD-3-Clause, Apache-2.0);
their notices are preserved inline within ui.js and sw.js.
